app: add HighlightRuleSet runtime + extract MakeStringMatcher

Adds `HighlightRuleSet`, the runtime companion to
`LogConfiguration::highlightRules`. Owns the compiled per-rule
`RowPredicate` list plus a per-source-row "last matching rule
index" cache that `LogModel::data` will read from the paint hot
path (wired in a follow-up commit).

Key design points:
* **Column identity by keys.** Rules bind through
  `HighlightRule::columnKeys` -> resolved column index at compile
  time. `MoveColumn`, cross-source apply, and unrelated column
  additions do not disturb the rule set; unresolved rules become
  inert until the next `RebindColumns` observes a matching column.
* **Last-match-wins.** `EvaluateRows` walks rules in reverse; the
  first accepting rule wins per row. Vector order is meaningful
  and surfaces in the editor as Move-up / Move-down.
* **Compact match cache.** `mRowMatch` is `int16_t` per source
  row; 2 MB on a 1M-row log. `LastMatchFor` is a bounds-checked
  index lookup, ~O(1). `HasActiveRules` short-circuits sessions
  with no live rules.
* **Reused compilation logic.** Matches the existing
  `MainWindow::UpdateFilters` pipeline predicate-for-predicate,
  including Level-column enum expansion via `LevelRankCache` so
  a rule saved as `"Info"` still matches raw `"INFO"` payloads.

Extracts `MakeStringMatcher` (plus its `PrimeRegex` /
`HaystackQStringFast` helpers) from `main_window.cpp`'s anonymous
namespace into a new shared TU `log_string_matcher.{hpp,cpp}`. The
extracted overload takes `HighlightRule::Match` too (the two
enums mirror alternative-for-alternative on purpose, so the cast
is safe and pinned by the wire-format enum tests).

No behaviour change to filters -- the extraction is a pure code
move.
